{HEXA BREAKER}
■ Whenever this creature attacks, destroy 6 creatures. (Choose a maximum of 6, including your own creatures.)
■ This creature attacks if able.

■ Whenever one of your creatures would leave, put a seal on that creature instead.
{SEAL}
(To seal a card, put the top card of your deck on top of that card face down. Whenever a Command is put, its owner puts a seal from one of their cards that has the same civilization as that Command into their graveyard. Sealed creatures are ignored.)
(Whenever another D2 Field is put, put this D2 Field into your graveyard.)
D2 WRAP Denjara Switch: At the start of your turn, you may turn this D2 Field upside down for the rest of the game. If you do, you may put up to 6 seals into your graveyard.}

{DOUBLE BREAKER}
■ Your creatures' abilities that would trigger when your creatures are destroyed, trigger twice instead.
■ Whenever this creature attacks, you may destroy one of your other creatures. Then draw 2 cards.

{DOUBLE BREAKER}
■ When you put this creature, destroy 2 of your creatures. Then your opponent chooses one of their creatures and destroys it.
■ You can't put other exile creatures that have "School" in their name into the battle zone.

{DOUBLE BREAKER}
■ When you put this creature, destroy 2 of your creatures. Then your opponent chooses one of their creatures and destroys it.
■ You can't put other exile creatures that have "School" in their name into the battle zone.

{DOUBLE BREAKER}
■ When you put this creature, destroy 2 of your creatures. Then your opponent chooses one of their creatures and destroys it.
■ You can't put other exile creatures that have "School" in their name into the battle zone.

{TRIPLE BREAKER}
■ When you put this creature, choose one of your opponent's creatures and destroy. Then choose a card from your opponent's mana zone and put it into its owner's graveyard.
■ Whenever your opponent puts a card into their graveyard from anywhere, you may put the top card of your deck into your mana zone.
